1712, and &s;ent &s;ome copies of it into England; one particularly to Mr. St.
Amand<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot"><HI>i. e.</HI> The Duke Marlborough's friend Berry.</NOTE>."</P>
<P>The letter is &s;igned Jo. Newman, Middleton and Caryll amu&s;ed them&s;elves
frequently with writing a <HI>jeu d'e&s;prit</HI> of this kind, which was probably well re|ceived
